levant to the language team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue."}, {"id": 630652267, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw2MzA2NTIyNjc=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/C-feature-request", "name": "C-feature-request", "color": "f5f1fd", "default": false, "description": "Category: A feature request, i.e: not implemented / a PR."}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 14, "created_at": "2017-02-14T02:25:07Z", "updated_at": "2023-02-15T22:50:12Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "This seems like it should work: [Playground link](https://is.gd/Q8MWVS)\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nuse std::sync::Arc;\r\n\r\ntrait Foo {}\r\n\r\nstruct Bar;\r\n\r\nimpl Foo for Bar {}\r\n\r\nfn takes_foo(foo: &Foo) {}\r\n\r\nfn main() {\r\n    let foo: Arc<Foo> = Arc::new(Bar);\r\n    takes_foo(&foo);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever, it seems the compiler is attempting to coerce `&Arc<Foo>` to a trait object before attempting deref coercion, which gives this unintuitive error:\r\n\r\n```\r\nrustc 1.15.1 (021bd294c 2017-02-08)\r\nerror[E0277]: the trait bound `std::sync::Arc<Foo>: Foo` is not satisfied\r\n  --> <anon>:13:15\r\n   |\r\n13 |     takes_foo(&foo);\r\n   |               ^^^^ the trait `Foo` is not implemented for `std::sync::Arc<Foo>`\r\n   |\r\n   = note: required for the cast to the object type `Foo`\r\n```\r\n\r\nAdding a deref-reref seems to fix the issue, but it's definitely a papercut:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\ntakes_foo(&*foo);\r\n```", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/39801/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/39801/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}